article.description: — Malik Miller recorded 13 points and 10 rebounds to lead Morgan State to a 60-47 win over Hampton on Monday night in the Chris Paul HBCU Challenge.
article.headline: Miller lifts Morgan St. over Hampton 60-47
article.linkText: Miller lifts Morgan St. over Hampton 60-47
article.story: PHOENIX -- — Malik Miller recorded 13 points and 10 rebounds to lead Morgan State to a 60-47 win over Hampton on Monday night in the Chris Paul HBCU Challenge. Seventh Woods had 12 points for Morgan State (3-5), which broke its five-game losing streak. Lagio Grantsaan added 10 points. Collin Nnamene had three blocks. Najee Garvin had 17 points for the Pirates (2-6), whose losing streak reached six games. Russell Dean added 14 points. Dajour Dickens had eight rebounds and three blocks. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
